<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="62" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,738,985]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,353,738,763]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Diagnosis. Male:</emphasis>
Forewing length 
<quantity box="[561,657,738,763]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="10.5">10.5mm</quantity>
. Nudum 
<number box="[765,796,739,763]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="12.0">12</number>
. DFW brand large, subapical spot yellowish, in R 
<number box="[1379,1387,753,767]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="5.0">5</number>
-M 
<number box="[1421,1429,753,767]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
. VFW costal area, apical spot and marginal band homogeneous yellowish. VHW with faint yellowish discal band and streak in CuA 
<number box="[365,373,828,842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
- 
<number box="[381,396,814,838]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
A. Median apophyses of tegumen developed, large, simple, with a proximal constriction; lateral processes pointed. Harpe thin, curved. Ventro-posterior end of aedeagus truncated.
</paragraph>
